      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Metronidazole, a common antibiotic for tooth infections, is a no-go for wine consumption. The combination of metronidazole and alcohol can cause a nasty reaction, including stomach cramps, diarrhea, and even a potentially life-threatening condition called methemoglobinemia. I'd recommend waiting until you've finished the full course of meds, and then you can indulge in a glass or two of wine. Just be sure to drink it slowly and in moderation, and don't overdo it, or you might end up with a headache the size of your tooth!",
